org.hl7.vmr.r2

Class ProcedureProposal

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hl7.vmr.r2.ClinicalStatement
      • org.hl7.vmr.r2.ProcedureBase
        • org.hl7.vmr.r2.ProcedureProposal
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ImagingProposal, LaboratoryProposal, RadiotherapyProposal, RespiratoryCareProposal

    public class ProcedureProposal
extends ProcedureBase
    Proposals for a procedure to take place, e.g., generated by a CDS system or by a consulting clinician. Proposals for making an observation (e.g., Pneumonia Severity Index, blood pressure, or PHQ-9 Depression Assessment) are also included in the scope of ProcedureProposal.

    Java class for ProcedureProposal complex type.

    The following schema fragment specifies the expected content contained within this class. 

     <complexType name="ProcedureProposal">
   <complexContent>
     <extension base="{urn:hl7-org:vmr:r2}ProcedureBase">
       <sequence>
         <element name="proposedProcedureTime" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}IVL_TS" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="frequency" type="{urn:hl7-org:vmr:r2}Schedule" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="prnReason" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}CD" maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="reason" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}CD" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="urgency" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}CD" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="originationMode" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}CD" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="proposalEventTime" type="{urn:hl7-org:cdsdt:r2}IVL_TS" minOccurs="0"/>
       </sequence>
     </extension>
   </complexContent>
 </complexType>

      • getPrnReason

        public List<CD> getPrnReason()
        Gets the value of the prnReason property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the prnReason property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getPrnReason().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list CD
